          "text": "Clear. That segment is effectively a fullscreen pre-staged mini-app with roughly 15-20 advance steps (wrong answer, rollback, thinking opens, code block, run, error, fix, re-run, validate, final answer, second question, searches, source excerpts, compiled answer). Structural implication: presentation navigation becomes a flat script where each step is either a camera move (pan to next segment, zoom to a detail) or a segment-internal advance. Same key/click drives both - the presenter doesn't think about which mode they're in. Two decisions I'd like pinned before I rewrite `design_guide.md` an…"
