          "kind": "assistant",
          "text": "Found it. The `transform: translateX(-300px)` on `.chat-column` turns chat-column into a containing block, which makes it the `offsetParent` for its staged children. So `last.offsetTop` is measured relative to chat-column (not chat-root), losing the ~650px of header/padding above it - which pushes the computed target below `minY` and the camera gets clamped to the segment top. Fix: walk the `offsetParent` chain up to `rootEl` and sum. Same for the zoom-target measurements."
